### 1. Create a New Employee (Must be in YOUR warehouse)
POST {{baseUrl}}/create
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Vikram Patil",
  "email": "vikram.patil@mailinator.com",
  "contactNumber": "1253078945",
  "warehouseId": "{{warehouseId}}"
}

### 2. Get All Users (Returns only users in your Warehouse)
GET {{baseUrl}}/all
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### 3. Get All Active Users
GET {{baseUrl}}/all-active
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### 4. Update User Status (ADMIN ONLY) (If you use a MANAGER token, this should return 403 Forbidden)

PATCH {{baseUrl}}/status?id={{userId}}&status=ACTIVE
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### 5. Get User by ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/{{userId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### 6. Get Users by Role (Filtered by your Warehouse)
GET {{baseUrl}}/role/EMPLOYEE
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### 7. Update User Details (ADMIN ONLY)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/{{userId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Shri Updated",
  "role": "MANAGER"
}

### 8. Delete User (ADMIN ONLY)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/{{userId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### 9. Security Test: Cross-Warehouse Access (Try to access a User ID that belongs to a DIFFERENT warehouse) (Expected: 401 Unauthorized (from Service Layer validateWarehouseAccess))
GET {{baseUrl}}/USER_ID_FROM_OTHER_WAREHOUSE
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}